                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; a few lines on
                           the incipit page of Text I, alternating with black lines; incipit of each
                           section of Text I; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 32rb,
                           34va, 36rb); abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements
                           of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 5rb,
                           6ra), halle luya (e.g., fols. 8ra, 11rb), wa-yǝbälu ḥǝzb (e.g., fols.
                           12ra, 13ra), kǝśtat (e.g., fols. 30ra, 71va), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols.
                           33vb, 35ra), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 36rb, 38ra).</seg>
